The big surprise with this inexpensive investment is how many solitaire related games line the path to the one you like.  Maybe you will discover some new favorites here.  All of the variations have the rules built in, along with suggested moves and an undo feature to try some options.  The extra features are impressive.  You can also start an instance of each variation and leave it unfinished to try a different game out.  Then you can return to any of the games later to complete or restart each when you like.  The only bother to me was that the 2 variations of Klondike are very difficult to win.  One is the 3 card deal option, while the other deals single cards but you only get one shot at using them or work your way backwards through the discards, casino rules.  It took me 20 games to win one, but that did feel good to accomplish.  Ok, I whine too much.  This collection is great.
